{"page":1,"prev_page_endpoint":null,"next_page_endpoint":null,"total_pages":1,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2012-10-31T07:07:26Z","content":"We only cheat ourselves by not demanding greater choice.","like_count":4,"author_name":"Linda myeres","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32658272"},{"created_at":"2012-10-29T23:08:47Z","content":"The state of the country today is the resume of the Democrats and Republicans....we need to get rid of them both.","like_count":4,"author_name":"Charles Bell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32562899"},{"created_at":"2012-10-28T03:53:14Z","content":"It is very important to have all viable candidates participate in debates. It forces the major parties to address issues raised by the third parties and lets the public know about options the major parties ignore.","like_count":4,"author_name":"Cherie  Gorman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/782350"},{"created_at":"2012-10-31T06:42:54Z","content":"we need to break up this Duopoly over the election system!","like_count":3,"author_name":"megan nguyen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2460890"},{"created_at":"2012-10-31T07:14:00Z","content":"It is important to get issues of concern on the table and in the public eye that neither the Dems nor Repubs dare to touch","like_count":3,"author_name":"Anne Jackson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7529857"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T16:20:46Z","content":"Our two-party system is hardly representative of the variety of views and political stances Americans hold and because of that what we get is a system in which we have political stagnancy, many Americans feeling like their views aren't being represented, and a lack of faith in our electoral system.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Alicia Clegg","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32178914"},{"created_at":"2012-10-30T20:25:46Z","content":"There is now only one party it has two names but it is all the same.  We need a party that represents the PEOPLE not corporations.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Jackie Shelton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6832449"},{"created_at":"2012-10-29T23:14:33Z","content":"We need more choices and chances for better solutions.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Cindy Brady","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32563174"},{"created_at":"2013-03-26T18:14:59Z","content":"This whole \"lesser of two evils\" bullshit needs to come to an end!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Christopher Kynaston","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45379555"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T23:18:04Z","content":"We need new perspectives for better solutions. The ones they have - have failed the people.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Armando Ortiz","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32214496"},{"created_at":"2012-10-28T09:05:25Z","content":"A third party option would force the dialogue to expand.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Cheryl Caputo","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32450121"},{"created_at":"2012-10-26T08:39:36Z","content":"The current two-party system has stagnated into a deadlock, with most states already set, and election funds focused on a very small percentage of the actual population. Real issues are not discussed, and real positions are not taken. A third party option would force the dialogue to expand beyond cosmetic differences and really consider the content of the presidency. As a registered Independent, I think that we as a country owe it to our government to think deeply about the issues, and without a third party shakeup, this won't happen.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Deborah Pless","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15604069"},{"created_at":"2012-11-19T17:19:59Z","content":"Some people are not even aware that they have a choice beyond the two main parties. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"ashley simmons","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30328353"},{"created_at":"2012-10-31T13:58:54Z","content":"To foster an environment in which humans are not denied information and free-will through the corporate government takeover.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Katherine Venable","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32680723"},{"created_at":"2013-04-18T21:54:42Z","content":"The democrats and republicans no longer represent the American voice or choice in where this country is going.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Tim Simpson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47932062"},{"created_at":"2012-10-29T01:01:26Z","content":"The two party system is ruining this country.  we need to have the ability to know more about serious alternatives.","like_count":1,"author_name":"trish gorman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8708287"},{"created_at":"2013-03-26T18:02:39Z","content":"Gary Johnson 2016","like_count":1,"author_name":"Justin Bishop","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45378007"},{"created_at":"2012-10-25T10:35:00Z","content":"More voices to represent true range of American's","like_count":1,"author_name":"Bridie Macdonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32250072"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T02:19:57Z","content":"We need to end the duopoly. America deserves a better choice. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Lyn Brooks","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10374482"},{"created_at":"2012-10-21T10:44:59Z","content":"Because we need to have choices so that we have different perspectives. The state of the country today is a reflection of what only having two parties will do. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Debo Grim","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/debo"},{"created_at":"2012-10-31T12:28:12Z","content":"The Democrat and Republican Parties have become representatives of the corporations that support their campaigns. We need third party candidates that think of the people and the good of the nation first, not the demands of the corporations.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Debra Herter","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29962208"},{"created_at":"2012-10-31T12:47:20Z","content":"There are more than 2 Parties in this country and the country needs to know this.  I am voting Green this year because I do not care for Obama or Romney.  They are NOT our only option.  Both complain that we are trillions of dollars in debt, yet waste millions on campaigning and debating. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Adam Youker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32675961"},{"created_at":"2012-10-25T07:39:02Z","content":"The two-party system is broken","like_count":1,"author_name":"Lisa Tannebaum","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32241243"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T17:56:50Z","content":"Because decisions as important as those which Presidents make should probably not be limited to only two... (Duh)","like_count":1,"author_name":"Ben Wilson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11562778"},{"created_at":"2012-10-28T09:15:17Z","content":"We need better solutions.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Mary McCabe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32450428"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T07:56:25Z","content":"It's needed.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jim Bellheart","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8291139"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T00:09:47Z","content":"Americans deserve more choices; those choices need to be taken seriously, and being barred from the debates chips away at their credibility in the eyes of the American people.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ariana Eakle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20500882"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T03:03:44Z","content":"We need to end the duolopoly and have a true democracy.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Natasha Hedlund","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10228000"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T16:24:33Z","content":"Our country and world must contain as many voices as possible. Two parties, in there present condition, is just a form of totalitarianism. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sharon Riegie Maynard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/sriegie"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T02:40:35Z","content":"We need more options. There are more than 2 nearly identical parties.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Eric Ward","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7724490"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T15:12:23Z","content":"Also, please work on laws that make ballot access easier for all...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kennon Gilson & Family","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21764697"},{"created_at":"2012-11-25T22:50:20Z","content":"I consider myself a moderate. Unfortunately, given the recent radicalization of the Republican Party, from attempting to redefine the crime of rape, to blatant refusal to cooperate on Capitol Hill, has led me to go against them as a party. It's time we replace the Republicans entirely.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Daniel Boodry","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35062582"},{"created_at":"2013-01-26T12:28:05Z","content":"Because we as Americans deserve more choice. We as America NEED more choice as we move forward.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brenda Robichaud","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11713465"},{"created_at":"2013-03-26T19:03:01Z","content":"as a \"third party\" voter for over 25 years, I feel we need representation, too!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Fred Valenzano","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45385662"},{"created_at":"2012-11-03T09:39:02Z","content":"Democracy?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Josh Shulman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15898871"},{"created_at":"2012-11-26T04:35:20Z","content":"We do not have freedom to choose if our choices are limited. There may be a better candidate who does not belong to the Democratic or Republican parties. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Deidra Hardimon Young","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35074341"},{"created_at":"2012-11-05T19:35:59Z","content":"We should have the ability to see ALL eligible candidates presented equally, not be forced to vote for crap because the system won't allow a real candidate to win.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Casey B","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2021613"},{"created_at":"2012-10-26T01:21:56Z","content":"We need third party candidates for a more true democracy.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lynette Jandl","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/465425"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T22:13:51Z","content":"Freedom.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Constance Taunton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32033635"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T06:30:29Z","content":"We need to have more option and different outlooks.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Suzy Skinner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31976278"},{"created_at":"2012-11-22T03:04:55Z","content":"We need more choices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"randy walters","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34797106"},{"created_at":"2012-10-26T20:24:49Z","content":"I support freedom.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ismaila Singley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6275170"},{"created_at":"2013-01-05T09:00:51Z","content":"It's time for a new pair of eyes, America.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carl Kazmirek","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/38002556"},{"created_at":"2012-11-02T00:26:25Z","content":"Better solutions to the countries problems.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Geary","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32784315"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T22:22:40Z","content":"The 2016 election will be the first election I vote in. I am very well rounded in politics but my friends aren't so when they watch the debates I want to make sure they know who they want to vote for out of all the candidates not just the main two.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andrew Kramer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26213810"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T11:31:14Z","content":"For the continuation of a Democracy, not a plutocracy.  To allow free elections, not corporate owned elections.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alex Watson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29462853"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T05:48:58Z","content":"I feel that people need to be informed of all their options when it comes to voting for something as important as the Presidency.  I want to ensure that my fellow countrymen know that there is an alternative to only right or left.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bonnie Williams","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7972946"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T02:26:31Z","content":"This is important to me because the people of the United States of America need a true choice!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mike Cushist","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10589868"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T13:31:23Z","content":"Even if they represent smaller numbers of citizens, third/fourth/fifth party candidates can and do bring important issues to the forefront.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chrysteen Moelter-Gray","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2045528"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T11:52:24Z","content":"In a two party system, we are forced to hedge our bets by voting against the person we don't want to win, rather than on the person we do want to win.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nathaniel Summers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30943881"},{"created_at":"2012-10-28T08:53:12Z","content":"Americans need more choices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jamal King","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32449751"},{"created_at":"2013-03-26T18:49:47Z","content":"No difference in the two parties--both owned by big money.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Colleen Esra","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7991942"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T00:37:28Z","content":"This is important if this truly is a democracy.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Niru Philip","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32042389"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T06:05:03Z","content":"I would like to one day exercise my right to vote for whomever I think is the best candidate, not the lesser of two evils.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Pressman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1135979"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T16:50:35Z","content":"I'm a huge supporter of third parties and third party suppression like keeping them out of the debates, is one of the things that prevents them from being voted in. They do have a chance they just need to be given it by the people.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ryan Patrick Logan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/19830092"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T15:03:02Z","content":"We the people are not always represented by the Republican and Democratic parties. We have a perfect example of the problem this year, when the Republican party has allowed itself to be entirely overrun and its validity and viability ruined by Tea Party radical extremists. There are other choices out there and the spirit of Democracy calls for others to be allowed to join the debates. The Democratic Party has been holding up, but humanity is immature and our culture is immature. We need a broad spectrum of choices to avoid extremism. N.E.E.D. We need this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rebecca Martin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9895360"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T01:16:22Z","content":"our democracy has been corrupted","like_count":0,"author_name":"lois Arata","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2468008"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T06:05:13Z","content":"We must hear all the voices, not just the powerful, entrenched voices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dan Middleton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/23404625"},{"created_at":"2012-10-26T06:44:28Z","content":"The fact that two dominating parties force others to the sideline is not the same as having a \"two party system\". It was never designed to be a 2 party system.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Layton Washburn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21024991"},{"created_at":"2012-11-08T01:36:24Z","content":"We need to hear all the options available to us.  Give us a chance to take less government in order to have a better life!","like_count":0,"author_name":"cheri  manternach","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17017119"},{"created_at":"2013-03-26T18:02:24Z","content":"The two party system has gotten us this far.  o_O","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chris Roberts","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9760757"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T16:22:28Z","content":"Voters need to see ALL of their choices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joseph Spencer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/23085913"},{"created_at":"2013-03-26T18:36:41Z","content":"Clearly the Libertarian party needs to be heard because the MSM won't allow them to be heard because people would fall in love to easily.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kirk Landreneau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45382462"},{"created_at":"2012-10-31T09:45:41Z","content":"Diminish corporate influence.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janice Rhodes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17028205"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T02:11:08Z","content":"A large portion of America is unrepresented by the Democrats and Republicans. Elections are a sham unless third parties begin getting media coverage and debate inclusion, and in some cases ballot inclusion.","like_count":0,"author_name":"erik martin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32049628"},{"created_at":"2012-10-28T08:41:29Z","content":"Third parties bring more to the country.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Briana Mccrumb","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30499803"},{"created_at":"2012-11-09T22:24:45Z","content":"Maybe they will be forced to answer some real questions that the american people want answered !!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"BRIAN WILLIAMS","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33589243"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T23:15:00Z","content":"How can we NOT have choice when it comes to something so important?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andrea Douglas","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32214216"},{"created_at":"2013-03-26T18:16:00Z","content":"Tired of the same old politicians that work against the people. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Randy Schroeder","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45379707"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T04:03:05Z","content":"because we need real choices, different perspectives","like_count":0,"author_name":"evelyn link","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9240042"},{"created_at":"2012-10-28T07:50:40Z","content":"Its important for the country.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer coleman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32448083"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T07:18:18Z","content":"We have to have more options-look at the country.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ricky Williams","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32063185"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T11:12:16Z","content":"More people in the debate will help keep everyone honest and focused on their plans instead of attacks.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cosima Zehring","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32157750"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T06:30:39Z","content":"To choose best canidate\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Connie Lairmore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31867722"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T10:38:49Z","content":"Because we need to end the 2 party system and have choices when voting!!! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tina Whitt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32073196"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T23:11:35Z","content":"We need to open the field of possibility plus we have seen what the two parties can do- look at the country! Democrats and republicans both have failed. No need to keep repeating.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hay Pearson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32213906"},{"created_at":"2012-10-25T20:38:53Z","content":"This is important because neither of the mainstream candidates seem to understand how to read the constitution of the United States of America","like_count":0,"author_name":"Isaac Stone","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22526717"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T17:49:49Z","content":"People need to know who every candidate is. The 2 party system is artificial and doesn't work for the people--unless you count corporations as people, but not humans. 3rd party candidates have new and better ideas, are more interesting, and much funnier. I didn't sleep through the 3rd party debates.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linde Knighton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7797236"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T00:12:05Z","content":"I am tired of hearing Republicans say they are going to make Obama a one term president and Harry Reid not letting bills from the house even be voted on One person should not have so much power.  Any viable candidate deserves to be heard if their views follow the Constitution","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rosemary Hodges","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32129125"},{"created_at":"2013-10-06T01:28:31Z","content":"All political parties should be equally represented.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chad Adams","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13329477"},{"created_at":"2012-10-27T11:04:40Z","content":"We have seen what the two can do - look at the country! Lets see what others can do.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sara Benson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32401569"},{"created_at":"2012-10-28T08:56:50Z","content":"More candidates will keep the issues on the country.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tony Reynolds","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32449846"},{"created_at":"2012-10-25T00:30:32Z","content":"The two-party system is broken - the extremists of both parties dictate the party platforms and those of us in the middle aren't being represented.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dante Bacani","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32219767"},{"created_at":"2012-10-25T16:22:51Z","content":"Its the only way we can create greater possibility for greater solutions.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tom Crawford","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32273669"},{"created_at":"2012-10-25T16:18:34Z","content":"We need change.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mary Baker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32273262"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T17:50:03Z","content":"Two is NOT the best number","like_count":0,"author_name":"patricia crawford","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2351197"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T10:19:08Z","content":"People are being excluded from it thats wrong","like_count":0,"author_name":"Edna Townsend","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31986165"},{"created_at":"2012-11-07T15:26:59Z","content":"All candidates with the potential to win enough electoral votes to win should be equally represented in the debates.  Voting should be an educated decision, not a media manipulated event.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carly Brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1284758"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T02:36:12Z","content":"Pretty obvious anyone running and on enough ballots to win needs to be heard.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nadine Rosselle Robinson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27363932"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T05:57:19Z","content":"Because we need more options than a two party system. Campaign finance caps, etc. to make this a fair playing field to candidates without big money supporters.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ron Pitt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10567896"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T07:55:36Z","content":"I want everyone represented on the ballot to have their say so no one thinks there's only two choices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kortney Geeting","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1928987"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T09:54:17Z","content":"What we have doesn't cut it! We need choices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mark LAN","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31984965"},{"created_at":"2012-11-12T23:57:44Z","content":"Third parties, who do not owe favors to lobbyists need to be heard.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erik Sepulveda","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33870480"},{"created_at":"2012-10-25T23:00:02Z","content":"I believe our government needs a third political party to rise up and restore order to our system.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Blake Reed","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32307125"},{"created_at":"2012-10-27T01:57:51Z","content":"Because we are one party away from ... what?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kimberly Hammill","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8896830"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T16:11:46Z","content":"Neither the republican nor democratic party represents me, or many of the people I know. Most of my acquaintances are only voting for one or the other because we've become convinced a third or fourth party is impossible. The lock the two major parties have is doing a huge disservice to our country, failing the voters and holding us all back. We demand equitable elections and debates where more than just two views are considered.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Josh Gamble","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3040192"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T08:40:45Z","content":"Try the world a fair bit to make","like_count":0,"author_name":"Anne Spriuijt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31928473"},{"created_at":"2012-10-27T10:55:19Z","content":"Got to have more choices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Charlotte Wagner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32401186"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T10:39:54Z","content":"People have better ideas.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alice Pennington","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31987061"},{"created_at":"2013-08-28T15:14:57Z","content":"I am tired of there only being two parties that REALLY have a chance to get into the office.  At that you only have a choice of bad or worse.  With more parties involved in the debates, there is more of a chance to find someone who is truly for the people, and not lining his and his buddies' pockets.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Thomas Hesseling","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60670250"},{"created_at":"2014-02-22T22:09:25Z","content":"As you clearly stated. \"We the People need to elect our President, not have a choice over two evils.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Patrick Rheaume","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/82649278"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T10:49:20Z","content":"It's 2012 how can there only be 2 choices and why has it always been? Wake up America - we deserve more!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Logan Wade","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31987476"},{"created_at":"2013-09-14T21:34:42Z","content":"You have a very limited choices when it comes to electing a president","like_count":0,"author_name":"Phill Nash","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62548186"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T16:26:04Z","content":"Democracy. And to spread the opportunity of genuine progressive social and economic change.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Paul Schulkind","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/19988675"},{"created_at":"2012-10-26T17:18:55Z","content":"Because we have Freedom of the Press,Freedom of Speech, and it is not being used. Come on People, be informed. Do you really want to elect someone who controls what you hear and see?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dianne Boggs","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28063214"},{"created_at":"2012-11-10T23:10:25Z","content":"i personaly do not believe in democratic or republican parties","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristpherson eberhardt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33666294"},{"created_at":"2012-10-27T11:07:02Z","content":"We have to change it.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rod Spinner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32401663"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T06:26:00Z","content":"Greater choice!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Randy Stanton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31976137"},{"created_at":"2012-10-27T23:12:58Z","content":"There are more than 2 sides to every answer...and a 3rd party is the right answer!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jon Sicotte","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32435847"},{"created_at":"2014-02-18T04:40:04Z","content":"All views need to be heard and not ignored. This gives the opportunity for wider topics of discussions and solutions.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Trina Bashore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8805314"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T21:23:18Z","content":"We need more choices!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Raynee Jolson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32030033"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T10:12:48Z","content":"We need something new.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Timothy Bennett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31985853"},{"created_at":"2012-10-27T03:29:51Z","content":"Greater solutions.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Charles Kenney","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32388115"},{"created_at":"2012-10-26T06:38:05Z","content":"CPD control of the presidential debates has harmed our democracy. \r\nWith no choices you end up with bought candidates that give little care for the people of the country. More Choice - better solutions. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hollis Reynolds","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32327754"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T19:32:24Z","content":"More voices equal more choices","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ted Pfeiff","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1104228"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T00:08:25Z","content":"Co-chair Green Party of VA","like_count":0,"author_name":"Audrey Clement","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1710004"},{"created_at":"2012-11-07T17:41:54Z","content":"Equal rights to all parties envolved and so people can make educated decisions about the people that are running for office.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Melissa Johnson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33274226"},{"created_at":"2012-10-25T23:01:33Z","content":"The Republican and Democratic Parties no longer preserve and protect America's people or their values. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cheri Greenway","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13951625"},{"created_at":"2013-03-26T18:00:25Z","content":"To open up the electoral process","like_count":0,"author_name":"George Gori","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45377746"},{"created_at":"2012-10-26T01:34:53Z","content":"The two party system does not allow for a true representation of the people of the US and there are many questions that go unanswered in the current system.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christine McDoough","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2813316"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T04:22:55Z","content":"Because America needs to be aware there are more than 2 parties to choose from- it's our right. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessie Dijkstra","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1065073"},{"created_at":"2014-02-20T00:23:09Z","content":"Love","like_count":0,"author_name":"Darik Thorson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/59710740"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T20:42:23Z","content":"While third party candidates generally viewed as only surrounding their attention around special interests, inclusion in the Presidential debates will expose voters to the array of ideas that third-party candidates may have to offer. Inclusion will also incent these candidates to expand their focus where they may not have previously given it. Finally, media enouragement of a two-party system is counter to what the founders of this country wanted. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alexander Gamble","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32009888"},{"created_at":"2012-10-29T22:59:26Z","content":"We need other alternatives.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sylvia Vinson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32562439"},{"created_at":"2012-11-27T22:17:14Z","content":"The masses are ignorant of the options they have when voting, as third party candidates cannot afford ad campaigns in the corporate media without corporate support. Third party candidates are not corporate owned, and thus are free to support policies for the benefit of the people, unlike Republicans and Democrats who serve only the corporate masters who own them. Letting other voices into the debate would get enough people interested in candidates that actually have the same goals that they do to vote, and bring about positive change in the system. This is why I don't think that this will ever be allowed to happen, regardless of this petition.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mark Baland","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11115372"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T06:11:31Z","content":"I believe the two party system, in spite of the venomous banter between them, has become stagnant and unproductive. More parties given a chance at the national stage will require a different kind of engagement. The future is now and we need to make some big decisions in the near future and a polarized country is not a good idea for any of us.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"kimmie hart","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7906382"},{"created_at":"2013-03-26T18:05:01Z","content":"The two party system needs a run for their money. Introducing third parties will also give people the opportunity to get a different perspective on the issues. Enough of the \"status quo\".","like_count":0,"author_name":"Audrey Barrett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30245539"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T06:36:08Z","content":"our \"2 party\" system sucks, but the time to stand up is not 2 months before the election when so much is at stake. Start now to create an environment where in 2016 third, fourth and fifth parties are viable and represented.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julie French","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/406252"},{"created_at":"2012-11-27T09:40:14Z","content":"Im sick of having two terrible candidates and no one to represent anything remotely near what i want. so many people dont like either candidate and feel they must vote for the lesser of two evils.people need choices. This is not a government that is representing the people.\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jonathan Brenneman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1029935"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T09:48:03Z","content":"The fact that third parties are forbidden, shows that the establishment has already chosen for us, and frankly I'm getting sick of this whole rigged show. What are they going to do when the whole USA is turning to Alex Jones? Because it's happening more and more. They cannot rig this forever. Once we see Alex Jones ratings get to a certain level, then we will undoubtedly know the current two party system should not be there anymore. It will be Constitutionalists and Libertarians battling it out. Not only this, but the whole country can turn on a dime if a third party blows the other candidates out of the water in the debate.\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Charles Waid","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31984675"},{"created_at":"2012-10-26T01:03:19Z","content":"We must revamp our corporatacracy now!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Pultz","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32313926"},{"created_at":"2012-11-06T16:43:18Z","content":"We the people deserve to hear all parties and all parties deserve to be heard! It is time to get rid of the 2 party system, it isn't working for America anymore!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Meagan Blackwood","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32089690"},{"created_at":"2012-11-02T20:44:19Z","content":"Presidential election debates have become just another reality television show, and poison to watch. The presidential debate ought to be informative and worth the time of the citizens of the United States of America to watch. Allowing Third Party Candidates to debate alongside the Republican and Democrat Candidates would allow for voters to make a better informed choice when they go to the polls. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Celene Cook","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32852581"},{"created_at":"2012-11-08T12:07:40Z","content":"I'm so tired of having to choose the lesser of two evils.  Give people all their options.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tania Walton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3611665"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T11:49:46Z","content":"A proper republic requires an informed citizenry.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Scott Forman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32159924"},{"created_at":"2012-11-27T22:34:00Z","content":"Both sides have ambitions to \"disenfranchise\" voters who disagree with their supremacist ideology, and convince them their vote doesn't count so they will give-up and quit voting. Allowing the third party to participate will stop this self-destruction by giving the life blood of America the recognition and support it needs in order to believe in this system of representation.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Denny Bissell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7992872"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T06:46:40Z","content":"Citizens of the United States of America deserve to hear every option they have for public officials.  To not allow more than two groups to represent ideas on how our country should be ran we destroying our future and not allowing for the much needed framework of democracy: Dissent and Discourcse","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shane Levy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16853664"},{"created_at":"2013-10-10T01:39:13Z","content":"Theodore F. Sawchak","like_count":0,"author_name":"Theodore Sawchak","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/65144046"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T23:59:07Z","content":"The system is clearly broken, and has been for a long time.  When a single party, like the communists, have a monopoly on the political process we rightly say that is a bad thing.  But how is a two-party duopoly significantly better?  That's closer to autocracy than democracy.  As is the treatment of third parties by both our electoral system and mainstream media.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andrew Trapp","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8262674"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T10:32:27Z","content":"It is just unbelievable that we live under the Constitution, and people's voices are still stifled.\r\n\r\nI can understand there having to be a line drawn somewhere, so that the national stage is not just a circus, but presidential candidates that have met a reasonable set of requirements, should be allowed to contribute their voices to the national debate. As this election has pointed out, there are clearly a number of issues that need to be dealt with in this country, so having people willing to give voice to those issues on a national stage and provide a separate, distinct viewpoint is valuable.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Edward Cooper","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13348658"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T21:37:50Z","content":"We need real debates, with real questions and thoughtful and thought provoking answers. All Americans have a right to know who the candidates are and to listen to answers that are more than just soundbites.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sheri Senft","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32031055"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T11:46:55Z","content":"Our problems cannot best be solved if only two voices are ever heard.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kenneth Sharp","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32076883"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T21:55:05Z","content":"A republic only can flourish when diverse viewpoints and creative ideas are part of the public dialogue.","like_count":0,"author_name":"James Paprocki","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/830737"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T02:49:42Z","content":"End the Staus Quo - LIVE FREE! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joe Sanchez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10371760"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T01:04:46Z","content":"The Democrats and Republicans have driven this country to the edge of the cliff. Time to give third parties the attention they deserve. <a href=\"http://justicepartyusa.org\" rel=\"nofollow\">justicepartyusa.org</a>","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laura Bonham","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9899"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T05:36:12Z","content":"Why should the American people only be shown two options?  Those two options have not worked in the past.  We need something new.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andrea Davis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25140926"},{"created_at":"2012-10-26T18:57:00Z","content":"I am a true believer in the 3rd-party as intended by our founding fathers.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gabriel Young","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32366465"},{"created_at":"2012-10-25T06:44:37Z","content":"This country needs choices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Larry Arvis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32238627"},{"created_at":"2012-11-11T06:34:17Z","content":"Two party system is corrupted.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Josefina Quiles","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6837467"},{"created_at":"2013-03-25T22:31:09Z","content":"We need better choices!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janet Levine","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45276312"},{"created_at":"2012-11-06T20:46:55Z","content":"America is supposed to a land of opportunity and a choice between two very like-minded people is hardly a choice at all.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bridget McHugh","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33162999"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T21:20:34Z","content":"This country needs serious change and instead of repeating history time and time again we need to change our response. We should be able to hear the voices of other Presidential candidates that are hidden behind all the money and media.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amanda Faronea","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32029809"},{"created_at":"2012-10-23T07:14:46Z","content":"Having choices is democracy at work.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sammy Levine","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32063045"},{"created_at":"2012-10-22T16:19:01Z","content":"All candidates should have the opportunity to present their issues along side each and engage in debate. This helps citizens to make the best, informed, personal decision they can.  Allowing only 2 candidates to debate creates an illusion that they are the only candidates available and or viable.  It's a complete disservice to the American citizens, their country and their government and political systems. It's criminal.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Vivica Valle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32005767"},{"created_at":"2012-10-24T06:02:43Z","content":"Because we're not a monarchy!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karl Schmitt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30442980"},{"created_at":"2012-11-27T01:13:24Z","content":"For too long we have been held prisoner to the two party debate system.  Choose to have choice!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Regina Sabin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7662014"}]}
